This paper is about analyzing adverse events in robotic surgery, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of natural language processing to analyze data from the FDA database also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves analyzing data from a large database, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for improved mechanisms for adverse event reporting, which could fall under the category of other computer science (cs.OH).
